  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Esophageal cancer is a highly aggressive malignancy with a poor overall outcome.

        -  Five year survival rate after radical esophagectomy is modest at about 40%.The patients
           with regional lymph node metastases have worse outcome than those without lymph node
           metastases.

        -  No standard postoperative adjuvant chemotherapy has ever been established.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
